Message.message: Hey, use that forklift to clear a path through these blocks to the back so we can unload the trucks.
If you mess up, drive up next to a gray terminal and hit [X] to reset the blocks to their original positions.
Each terminal only works on one color, so you'll have to hit both to reset everything.
It's inconvenient, I know, but the mark 2 terminals are still in the truck.
Hit [Z] to undo the last move, and hit [R] if you get extra stuck and want to reset everything from the beginning, including yourself.
Uh, and the extra flooring's all in the other truck. Sorry about that.
Great. After my lunch break, we can work on unloading everything.
This game is dedicated to all the PuzzleScripters out there who've had to fix a layer overwrite bug in their game logic. :]
Special shoutouts to PUZZLETALE by Connorses, which directly inspired this in two ways.
